		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/07/30/today-in-small-business-buy-nearby-guy/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Buy Nearby Guy" data-description="Second-quarter economic growth tops estimates. Four signs that an employee is going to quit. Should used-car dealers be allowed to sell cars with safety defects?">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The economy beat second-quarter estimates, growing at a <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/31/business/economy/us-economy-grew-4-in-second-quarter.html">4 percent annual rate</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ <a href="//www.rawstory.com/rs/2014/07/29/us-consumer-confidence-jumps-in-july/">Consumer confidence</a> jumped in July.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The debate about the <a href="//nyti.ms/1o0eYmf">Obama stimulus plan</a> is over &#8212; at least among economists.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Retail</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Retail groups <a href="https://nrf.com/news/nrf-asks-tokens-protect-credit-card-data">ask the credit card industry</a> to begin using âtokenizationâ technology that would replace card numbers with an encrypted code.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Michigan retailers are hoping a <a href="//www.wzzm13.com/story/news/features/2014/07/28/michigan-retailers-hope-to-get-a-hand-from-buy-nearby-guy/13283511/">new mascot</a>, dubbed Buy Nearby Guy, can help them compete with out-of-state, online sellers. <span id="more-87605"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Some retailers are using <a href="//www.cpapracticeadvisor.com/news/11597959/retailers-use-smartphone-coupons-to-increase-spontaneous-shopping">smartphone coupons</a> to encourage spontaneous shopping.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Finance</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Banks are willing to lend to small businesses, but a survey indicates that small businesses <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/blog/2014/07/small-businesses-can-get-loans-but-don-t-want-them.html">are still reluctant</a> to borrow.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The chief executive behind Diapers.com <a href="//venturebeat.com/2014/07/29/ceo-behind-diapers-com-raises-55m-for-a-mystery-ecommerce-venture/">has raised $55 million</a> for an e-commerce venture.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Management</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ General Mills is <a href="//money.cnn.com/2014/07/29/news/companies/general-mills-greenhouse-gas/index.html">insisting that its suppliers take steps</a> to cut greenhouse gas emissions as well as water use.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Employees</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Will the National Labor Relations Board&#8217;s McDonald&#8217;s ruling <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/30/business/nlrb-holds-mcdonalds-not-just-franchisees-liable-for-worker-treatment.html">open the door to fast-food unions</a>?</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here are four signs that <a href="//smallbusinessbonfire.com/4-signs-an-employee-is-quitting">an employee</a> is going to quit.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Some employers are <a href="//ebn.benefitnews.com/news/ebn_co_benefits_strategy/employer-take-to-meditation-as-a-perk-in-relaxing-staff-2742966-1.html">offering meditation</a> as a perk to help employees relax.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ After a &#8220;<a href="//www.eastbayexpress.com/WhatTheFork/archives/2014/07/29/after-a-staff-implosion-a-vegan-restaurant-tries-to-move-forward">staff implosion</a>,&#8221; the owner of a vegan restaurant in California is trying to move forward.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Social Media</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ LinkedIn <a href="//thenextweb.com/insider/2014/07/29/linkedin-revamps-user-profiles-help-increase-business-contacts/?a">revamps its user</a> profiles to help you increase your business contacts.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here&#8217;s how to use <a href="//www.socialmediaexaminer.com/twitter-analytics/?">Twitter analytics</a> to find important data.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Twitterâs <a href="//www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2014/07/29/twitter-earnings-beat-wallstreet/13291645/">stock</a> surges after strong quarterly results.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the Country</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ New York City doesn&#8217;t want used-car dealers to be able to sell cars that have been <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/30/business/new-york-city-imposes-a-used-car-repair-rule.html">recalled with safety defects</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Welcome to <a href="//www.theguardian.com/cities/2014/jul/28/-sp-welcome-williston-north-dakota-america-new-gold-rush-city?C">America&#8217;s new</a> gold rush city: Williston, N.D.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A business in California <a href="//www.cbsnews.com/videos/a-business-in-chico-california-receives-43000-tip/">receives</a> a $43,000 tip.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A scammer <a href="//eaglecountryonline.com/local-article/scammer-claims-owner-takes-business-4700/">claims to be</a> the owner of an Indiana store and steals $4,700.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ An Oregon business <a href="//www.business-opportunities.biz/2014/07/25/retirement-homes-for-chickens/?">is providing a</a> kind of retirement home for farm animals.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the World</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ New <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/30/world/europe/european-sanctions-russia.html">sanctions on Russia</a> are aimed at its oil reserves.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Marketing</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Hoping to rebound, Malaysia Airlines <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3033723/terminal-velocity/hoping-to-rebound-malaysia-airlines-weighs-name-change">weighs</a> a name change.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A former chief executive of Ogilvy &amp; Mather <a href="//blogs.hbr.org/2014/07/the-former-ceo-of-ogilvy-mather-on-personal-branding/">discusses her thoughts on</a> personal branding.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Washington</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A Senate bill proposes <a href="//www.reuters.com/article/2014/07/29/us-usa-nsa-congress-idUSKBN0FY1EM20140729">sweeping curbs</a> on surveillance.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Ideas</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A company based in India <a href="//www.buzzfeed.com/alejandroalba/india-based-company-has-created-the-worlds-first-smart-shoe">has created</a> smart shoes.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Opportunities</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Some 200 million people from China are <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/101874676">expected to travel</a> abroad each year by 2020.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Technology</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Apple <a href="//www.informationweek.com/software/enterprise-applications/apple-refreshes-macbook-pros-cuts-prices/d/d-id/1297645?">refreshes</a> the MacBook Pro and cuts prices.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ It turns out <a href="//www.wired.com/2014/07/keyme-let-me-break-in/">all you need</a> to invade a friendâs apartment is an off switch for your conscience and an iPhone.</p>
